    "updated_at": "2016-10-18T16:05:07Z",
    "body": "This is a ‘must have’ for controlling applications using keyboard.\n\nAlso note that on Linux (at least with GTK), **underscore** is used for accelerators. Regular underscore is inserted using [double underscore](https://developer.gnome.org/gtk3/unstable/GtkButton.html#gtk-button-new-with-mnemonic).\n\n``` javascript\ndialog.showMessageBox(getCurrentWindow(), {\n    'message': 'Accelerations demo.',\n    'buttons': ['O_K', 'G_o', '&Moo']\n});\n```\n\n![accel-demo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/705123/19484319/7b9c0072-9557-11e6-8591-ad30a32ab142.png)\n\nOS X seems to require manual setting of [keyEquivalent](https://developer.apple.com/reference/appkit/nsalert/1532992-buttons#discussion).\n"
  },
